=== EXTRACTION RULES ===

1. VERBATIM TEXT: The clause_text field must contain the EXACT text from the document. Do not paraphrase, summarize, or rephrase.
2. COMPLETE EXTRACTION: Extract EVERY clause in the document, not just those matching known categories. Clauses that do not match any category should be classified as "uncategorized".
3. GRANULARITY: Each distinct obligation, right, or provision should be its own clause. Do not merge unrelated provisions into a single clause. If a section contains multiple distinct provisions (e.g., a "General" section with force majeure, assignment, and severability), extract each as a separate clause.
4. SECTION REFERENCES: If the document uses section numbers (e.g., "Section 5.2", "Article III"), capture them in the section_reference field. If no section number exists, set section_reference to null.
5. CATEGORY MATCHING: Match clauses to categories based on their legal substance, not just their title. A clause titled "General Provisions" might contain a force majeure provision (category: "general") or a governing law provision (category: "dispute_resolution").
6. ONE CATEGORY PER CLAUSE: Each clause gets exactly one category. Choose the most specific match. If a clause touches multiple categories, choose the dominant one.
7. CLAUSE TITLES: Create descriptive, concise titles. Use the document's own heading if available. If no heading exists, create one based on the clause's primary subject (e.g., "Limitation of Liability", "Termination for Convenience", "IP Assignment").
8. DEFINITIONS: If the document has a definitions section, extract it as a single clause with category "uncategorized" and title "Definitions".
9. PREAMBLE: Extract the preamble or recitals as a single clause with category "uncategorized" and title "Preamble" or "Recitals".

=== ANTI-HALLUCINATION SAFEGUARDS ===

- You MUST NOT invent clauses that do not exist in the document.
- You MUST NOT add text to a clause that is not present in the original document.
- If you are unsure about a category assignment, default to "uncategorized".
- If a clause is ambiguous or unclear, extract it as-is and note the ambiguity in the _extraction_reasoning.

